NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|3@S by me is Stayman. Assuming you are not playing Lebensohl (where 2NT has a conventional meaning), all the bids between 2N and 3N are natural, except for the cue bid of 3@S. 3@S is (game forcing obviously) Stayman and shows 4 hearts. With 5+ hearts you can bid 3@H over 2@S. You are hoping partner will bid 4@H or 3N but suppose he can do neither (he has neither 4 hearts nor a spade stopper). Then you must be prepared for partner to bid 4C or 4D over 3S and know what you are going to do.|
